&lt;h2&gt;Director GTM Strategy: Land, Expand &amp;amp; Ecosystem&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: Pune&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to: VP, GTM Strategy &amp;amp; Operations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;As the Director of GTM Strategy (Land, Expand &amp;amp; Ecosystem), you are the strategic architect of Showpad’s growth engine. You own the &quot;Front-End&quot; of the revenue engine, ensuring our new business, expansion, and partner motions are optimized for scale. This is a &quot;Product Management&quot; style leadership role where your &quot;product&quot; is the sales motion itself. You define the benchmarks for success and identify the AI-driven interventions needed to help the field reach them. You lead a team of analysts and strategists while personally driving the strategic direction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic Benchmarking: Define and set the performance benchmarks for the Land &amp;amp; Expand motions (e.g., Target CAC, LTV/CAC ratios, Partner-sourced pipeline %). You own the &quot;Target&quot; that the field is aiming for.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrated Planning: Lead the annual and semi-annual planning cycles for the New Business, Expansion, and Partnership organizations, including capacity modeling and quota distribution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Agent Ideation &amp;amp; Scoping: Act as the &quot;Field Scout&quot; to identify high-friction manual tasks (e.g., prospecting research or partner lead routing). You define the &quot;Job to be Done&quot; and business logic for new AI Agents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Specialized Analysis: Own the &quot;Last-Mile&quot; analysis. Once the Insights team stabilizes a reporting tool, you perform deep-dives into territory health, partner attribution, and win/loss trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;UAT &amp;amp; Field Pilot: Lead User Acceptance Testing (UAT) for new AI tools. You run pilot groups with AEs and xDRs to ensure AI output is high-quality before global rollout.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enablement Partnership: Collaborate with the VP of Enablement on &quot;Problem Discovery&quot; to ensure S&amp;amp;O is solving the most pressing field friction points. You lead the strategic &quot;Why&quot; behind new tool rollouts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ecosystem Integration: Act as the lead for the Partnerships team, defining how partners show up in territories, lead routing, and attribution models to ensure a &quot;better together&quot; motion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stakeholder management: Become trusted advisor to Marketing, Sales and Finance leaders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team Leadership: Lead, coach, and develop a team of GTM analysts and strategists. Set clear objectives, manage performance, and ensure your team is focused on the highest-impact work. You are the &quot;player-coach&quot;—you set the strategic direction and ensure your team has the skills and support to execute.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience: 8+ years in Sales/Revenue Operations, Management Consulting, or GTM Strategy. Experience in a high-growth, PE-backed SaaS environment (Vista-style) is a major plus. Proven track record of building and managing high-performing teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Literacy: Advanced proficiency in Salesforce (SFDC) and Excel/Google Sheets. Ability to translate business needs into technical requirements for an Engineering team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic Thinking: Proven ability to design territory and quota models from scratch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Influence: Ability to challenge Sales and Partner leadership with data-backed insights while maintaining strong working relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;People Leadership: Experience coaching, developing, and retaining top analytical talent. You know how to set direction and get out of the way.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Abou

