&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Unleash the Power of the Apple Ecosystem: From SwiftUI to On-Device Intelligence.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Showpad, we don’t just build an app; we build a high-performance engine for the modern enterprise. We are looking for an iOS Engineering Intern who is ready to push the boundaries of what’s possible on a mobile device.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This isn&#39;t a &quot;maintenance&quot; internship. You’ll be at the forefront of the Apple Intelligence era, leveraging the latest system frameworks to integrate Apple Foundation Models and Small Language Models (SLMs) directly into our user experience — all while mastering the art of modern app architecture&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Mission&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As our iOS Intern, you will be at the intersection of robust engineering and experimental innovation. You won&#39;t just be writing code; you’ll be defining how enterprise users interact with AI and hardware.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Learn the Ecosystem: Learn the Cutting Edge: Go deep into Swift 6.2. You’ll navigate Strict Concurrency, master Actors, and leverage the latest compiler safety features to build high-performance, data-race-free applications.On-Device Intelligence: Research and implement Apple Foundation Models and Small Language Models (SLMs). You’ll explore how to run intelligence locally to ensure maximum privacy and offline performance.Modernize &amp;amp; Migrate: Take part in our strategic evolution from UIKit to SwiftUI. You will learn how to bridge these worlds, ensuring a seamless transition to a declarative future.Architectural Mindset: Apply Solid OOP principles and design patterns to ensure our code remains scalable, modular, and testable.The Mobility Frontier: Conduct Proof of Concepts (POCs) for CarPlay, researching how to extend the Showpad experience into the vehicle for sales professionals on the move.Immersive Tech: Explore the next generation of AR/3D capabilities, using the latest system APIs to transform how digital content is visualized in the real world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mentorship &amp;amp; Growth&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe that the best way to learn is by doing—supported by world-class guidance. You’ll work in a high-performance environment designed to level up your engineering maturity:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Migration Masterclass: Get hands-on experience refactoring a massive enterprise app. You’ll learn how to ship modern code within a complex, established infrastructure.Deep Tutoring: You will be paired with Senior Mentors who will provide real-time feedback on your code, helping you master Swift Concurrency (async/await) and avoid common memory management pitfalls.Code Review Culture: Experience a rigorous but supportive PR process. Learn to write code that isn&#39;t just functional, but clean, documented, and maintainable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We value computational thinking and a &quot;builder&quot; mindset over a long list of specific experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Swift Native: You have a strong curiosity of Swift and a passion for building beautiful interfaces in SwiftUI.AI Curiosity: You are fascinated by the shift toward Apple Intelligence and want to learn how to deploy models locally on iOS.OOP Fundamentals: You understand classes vs. structs, protocol-oriented programming, and why SOLID architecture is the key to enterprise success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What’s In It For You?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Real Innovation: Your POCs for on-device AI and CarPlay will directly influence our mobile roadmap.Production Skills: Gain experience with CI/CD pipelines, Swift Package Manager, and modular architecture.Professional Toolkit: Learn industry standards for ve

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt; This role is available for hybrid work (2 days on-site) from our office in Bucharest.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our data platform powers customer-facing embedded analytics that thousands of users rely on daily. But we&#39;re going further: Showpad is building a Revenue Intelligence engine that transforms raw signals — CRM data, email threads, call transcripts, and content engagement — into prescriptive AI guidance. You will be a foundational architect of the unified data intelligence layer that makes this engine possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will participate in the design of our Medallion architecture, star schemas, and data governance frameworks — and critically, you will help define how structured and unstructured knowledge is modeled, connected, and retrieved. Your goal is to build a platform so robust and intuitive that other teams are empowered to build high-quality downstream models with speed and autonomy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape how we model and connect revenue data — accounts, deals, contacts, content, and engagement signals — across both structured and &lt;strong&gt;semantic&lt;/strong&gt; layers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and evolve the &lt;strong&gt;ontology&lt;/strong&gt; that defines how entities relate, enabling relationship-aware reasoning beyond what traditional joins can offer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain a &lt;strong&gt;Knowledge Graph&lt;/strong&gt; that supports multi-hop inference and entity disambiguation across our Revenue Intelligence engine&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own our &lt;strong&gt;retrieval architecture&lt;/strong&gt; — choose the right approach for each use case, whether that&#39;s RAG, vector similarity, graph traversal, or structured search&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define how we ground &lt;strong&gt;LLM outputs&lt;/strong&gt; in proprietary data, ensuring AI features are accurate, explainable, and production-ready&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to our Medallion architecture, star schemas, and data catalog, keeping the foundation solid as we scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure our embedded analytics meet the demands of multi-tenant isolation, sub-second latency, and strict SLAs for white-labeled products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a go-to resource for cross-functional teams — setting standards, reviewing models, and helping others build confidently on top of the platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain data contracts, schema governance, and lineage practices that keep data trustworthy at every layer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Product and Engineering to turn complex business needs into clear, pragmatic technical roadmaps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
