&lt;h1&gt;Lead Salesforce Developer&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly skilled Lead Salesforce Developer to thrive as part of a small team. Your primary focus will be hands-on, mission-critical development, leveraging your mastery of the Apex programming language. You will be responsible for the &quot;heavy lifting&quot; — writing high-quality, bulkified Apex, developing Lightning Web Components (LWC), and ensuring the technical health of our Salesforce platform alongside your teammate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apex-First Development: Write clean, well-tested, and bulkified Apex code for complex business logic, triggers, and controllers, prioritizing performance and maintainability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Component Building: Develop and maintain responsive user interfaces using Lightning Web Components (LWC).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solution Implementation: Collaborate on the design and implement scalable, well-architected solutions that utilize both programmatic and declarative features.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Platform Governance: Enforce coding standards, manage metadata, and actively participate in DevOps processes (Git, CI/CD) with team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;System Integration: Implement robust integrations between Salesforce and our external tech stack using APIs and middleware.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data Strategy: Maintain data integrity and security models (Shield/Sharing) to ensure the system remains performant as we scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience: 8–12+ years in the Salesforce ecosystem, with a deep focus on hands-on development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Certifications: Platform Developer II is required. Application or System Architect certification is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apex Mastery: Deep expertise in programmatic Salesforce, including Triggers, Controllers, Asynchronous Apex, and comprehensive Unit Testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;LWC Expertise: Proven ability to build complex, responsive user interfaces using Lightning Web Components (LWC).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Declarative Excellence: Expert understanding of the Salesforce platform, knowing precisely when to utilize Flow versus custom Apex code for maintainability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrations: Expert knowledge of implementing integrations using REST/SOAP APIs, JSON, and OAuth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Security: Advanced understanding of the Salesforce Sharing Model, Profiles, Permission Sets, and Field Level Security as they pertain to code security.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaboration &amp;amp; Shared Ownership: A proven ability to work effectively on a small, high-output team, sharing responsibilities and maintaining code quality standards across the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pragmatism: You build for 2 years from now, not 20 years from now. You value speed-to-market without sacrificing system health.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communication: The ability to clearly articulate technical solutions and challenges, including explaining technical debt to stakeholders and defining requirements within the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Integration Engineer (Backend &amp;amp; Architecture)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a senior/lead role and a critical opportunity to anchor our newly formed internal Integrations team. You will design, architect, and govern the resilient backend services that connect the Showpad platform with leading SaaS ecosystems. You will be the primary technical gatekeeper, ensuring all backend architectures meet our stringent enterprise standards for security, scalability, and observability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Architectural Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; Author and submit Architecture Decision Records (ADRs) for all new integrations, ensuring alignment with event-driven, asynchronous models.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Backend Engineering:&lt;/strong&gt; Develop isolated, decoupled microservices strictly utilizing TypeScript and Go.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cloud Infrastructure:&lt;/strong&gt; Provision resources exclusively using AWS CDK (Infrastructure as Code) across multi-region environments. Implement and manage DynamoDB and Amazon Aurora RDS databases.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Resiliency &amp;amp; Eventing:&lt;/strong&gt; Build highly idempotent outbound APIs with exponential backoff algorithms. Architect strictly asynchronous webhook ingestion pipelines using AWS EventBridge and SQS.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enterprise Observability:&lt;/strong&gt; Instrument rich telemetry using OpenTelemetry standards. Design and deploy Datadog Out-of-the-Box (OOTB) dashboards to monitor crucial Service Level Indicators (SLIs) like availability, latency, and throughput.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Security &amp;amp; Compliance:&lt;/strong&gt; Ensure all services strictly enforce tenant isolation, align with GDPR data minimization strategies, and adhere to SOC 2 Type II cryptographic standards.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Readiness:&lt;/strong&gt; Guide the team through strict Operational Readiness Reviews (ORR) and ensure all CI/CD quality gates are successfully navigated prior to production releases.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a Bachelor’s Degree in Information Technology, Computer Science, or Software Engineering, plus 6+ years of software engineering experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You possess deep expertise in TypeScript and Go.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have extensive experience with AWS, specifically serverless architectures, CDK, EventBridge, SQS, and Secrets Manager.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are an expert in designing decoupled, event-driven architectures and understand the critical trade-offs of distributed systems.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are highly proficient in application observability (Datadog, OpenTelemetry, structured logging, distributed tracing).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have working knowledge of utilizing AI-first coding assistants.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt; Bucharest (hybrid 2x week in office)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Staff Engineer on the Data Fabric team, you won’t just write code, you will set the technical direction, solve the hardest problems, and mentor the next generation of engineers. This is a role for someone who thrives in ambiguity, sees patterns where others see chaos, and builds long-term solutions that keep our systems healthy, scalable, and resilient.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Senior Engineers are masters of their craft. Staff Engineers go a step further: you’ll tackle open-ended challenges where the right path isn’t obvious, drive technical strategy across multiple teams, mentor and sponsor engineers at every level, and be the one who makes complexity vanish—reducing technical debt and chaos with elegant, pragmatic solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead with vision: Shape technical roadmaps, explore new problem spaces, and set direction for initiatives that span across teams—with a particular focus on the Data Fabric domain.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a force multiplier: Mentor engineers at all levels, sponsor opportunities for growth, and foster a culture of technical excellence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reduce chaos: Design Angular/TypeScript solutions that simplify, scale, and improve long-term maintainability across the data platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive impact: Identify what matters most for Showpad’s future—whether it’s reducing infrastructure costs, building resilient data pipelines, or unlocking new product capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion quality: Advocate for resilience, performance, and security, ensuring we always raise the technical bar.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you our next Staff&amp;nbsp; Engineer?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Must haves&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience solving complex technical challenges (we know expertise doesn’t always fit neatly in a timeline—what matters is impact).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep, production-grade proficiency in &lt;strong&gt;Angular&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;TypeScript&lt;/strong&gt;, with a strong command of scalable front-end architecture, component design patterns, and performance optimization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with data-intensive applications—comfortable working across data fabric concepts, &lt;strong&gt;distributed systems&lt;/strong&gt;, or &lt;strong&gt;event-driven architectures&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record in technical leadership, architecture, and strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record for mentorship, clear communication, and long-term thinking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to see both the big picture and the fine detail, knowing when to zoom out to strategy and when to dive deep into technical issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pragmatism: you make deliberate decisions, balancing speed and sustainability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience working in &lt;strong&gt;AWS&lt;/strong&gt; environments—comfortable with core services (e.g. Lambda, S3, RDS, Kinesis) and cloud-native architectural patterns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open to engaging with backend topics—you’re not limited to the front end and can contribute meaningfully to full-stack conversations, API design, and data pipeline decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
